Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.24,0:00:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NOh dear. Oh dear. Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.63,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> We're going to be doing a little bit of\Ndialoguing um this afternoon. Can you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hear me? Okay. Oh, there we are. Um and\Nwe're going to be talking about living
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.56,0:00:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present and how you go about\Nliving in the present. Uh not in the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.08,0:00:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,future, not in the past, but living with\Nwhat's happening right now in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.67,0:00:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to be doing a little bit\Nof dialoguing on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.64,0:00:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, people liked the dialoguing we did\Nbefore, so we thought we'd
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.48,0:00:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>> try\N>> repeat it and see if they still like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And if not,\Nif not, we'll fold up our tent and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.96,0:00:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,silently slink away.\N>> Okay. So how does one um
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.07,0:01:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how does one let go of the past?\NHow do you let go of past um say
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.36,0:01:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,oh the effects of the past? How do you\Nlet go of the effects that the past has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.15,0:01:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,had on one's life?\N>> Well, you look at it as instant karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.84,0:01:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You just goofed up. Now you suffer. Huh?\NSo why protest the suffering that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.47,0:01:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself created? Of course, you always\Nblame it on somebody else,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.40,0:01:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.43,0:01:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you have a tendency to always say, well,\Nif you hadn't done that, I I wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have happened to me.\N>> That's true. Yeah. You want to get rid
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the the responsibility,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.36,0:01:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\NAnd the only the only way I I've
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.32,0:01:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered is is uh is for the mind to\Nbecome silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.68,0:02:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the mind is silent,\Nuh that answers the whole problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.75,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. How do you make the mind silent?\N>> Because we keep running this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,picture, you know, it keeps going on.\NThis whole picture in the back of your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.68,0:02:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,mind keeps happening. So how do you make\Nthe mind go? Well, like you said, the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,picture is either of the anticipation of\Nthe future. The mind never loses in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,present.\NIn order to survive, it has to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipate the future and it has to\Nregret the past. So, if you refuse those
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,payoffs, so those are payoffs.\NAnd uh in order to propagate itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.20,0:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what the ego hates is having nothing to\Ndo because then it's afraid it will no
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.72,0:02:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,longer exist.\NSo it keeps itself busy dreaming up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.59,0:02:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,problems for the future and inventing\Nregrets over the past. Of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:02:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,neither one of them has any reality\Nand therefore you stay in a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.95,0:03:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,non-reality.\NThe only way to let let have it all stop
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.56,0:03:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is to let go the desire to think, which\Nmeans letting go the pay payoff of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness.\NAnd the mind says, well, if you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,think and plan, you won't survive. So,\Nyou they really have to in a way give up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the will to survive.\NAnd you either survive or you don't. And
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,uh that's God's problem.\NWell, God created you, didn't he? So,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.79,0:03:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all right. So, you got to take\Nresponsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.36,0:03:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, you have to remind him once in a\Nwhile. I don't remember asking to be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.44,0:03:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,created, you know.\NIt was your idea. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Well, it wasn't my idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.79,0:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To create a world.\N>> That sounds a little too ambitious for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.95,0:04:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,me.\NIf I can get from here to there, I think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.92,0:04:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a good day.\NSo when your mind keeps replaying say a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.59,0:04:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um a tragic event that happened in your\Nlife the replay
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.56,0:04:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> so you know your mind has a tendency to\Nwant to replay that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.16,0:04:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So we're getting juice out of that\Nreplays it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.84,0:04:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So it's really the willingness to give\Nup the juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.52,0:04:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The payoff is the juice.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And that's the only fuel that the ego\Nhas is juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.40,0:04:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you deprive it of juice by being\Nwilling to let it go uh and and then
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,then the mind's faculties become\Njuiceless and when it's juiceless it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.16,0:04:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stops it abandons everything\Nand you live in silence. uh the inner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is silent\Nand uh so you stop identifying with the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:04:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,talkingness\Nand you see you become the witness so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.60,0:05:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say you stop participating in the\Nparticipating in the dialogue you become
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness of the dialogue I mean who's\Ncomplaining about the past or the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.75,0:05:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,present\Nu who is it that's complaining
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.12,0:05:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you well and how do you know what's\Ngoing on to let go identifying with the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.32,0:05:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dialogue and let go identifying with the\Nmind and become the witness of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.91,0:05:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you back off from identifying with\Nall the chitchat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and you realize how do I know what this\Nhow how do I even know there's chitchat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,going on? It's because of the observer.\NSo I always say the way out of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.47,0:05:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is to back out through the witness\Nobserver witness-observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.68,0:05:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh because that's not difficult to do.\NYou be you can begin to realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:06:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which I am is the witness, the observer\Nand not the participant. Because how do
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.60,0:06:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you're a participant? Because\Nyou witness it and observe it. So back
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.31,0:06:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,into identifying with\Nuh the witness observer and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then you go from witness observer to how\Ndo you know what is being witnessed and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.19,0:06:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,observed\Nand then you back up into awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.72,0:06:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,itself?\NThe only thing you're aware of is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.00,0:06:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. That's all you're aware of is\Nawareness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the awareness of what is\Nirrelevant because there's always
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,something you can be aware of.\NI remember that cartoon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.68,0:06:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from many years ago. I think it was a\NFleer's gum cartoon. Fleer's gum came
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.56,0:06:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with a cartoon on the rapper and and it\Nshows this kid and he's sitting on the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.24,0:06:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,curb and he's got a Fleer's gum wrapper.\NHe's so bored that he's reading the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.16,0:07:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rapper and he's reading all the\Ningredients in this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.00,0:07:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the gum, you know, reading,\Nyou know, so he's reading all the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,ingredients in this gum, you know,\Nbecause he's so bored. He doesn't he
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.63,0:07:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wants he's got to keep his mind busy. So\Neven a fleer's gum wrapper is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.80,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting when you're frantically\Nbored.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so when your mind starts to replay\Nthis tragedy and you start to s feel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry for what has happened, then what\Nyou what you're saying is that you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,should let it run its course or or try\Nand stop it before it starts. Well, once
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you become aware that what the ego is\Ndoing is constantly juicing things,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.12,0:07:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing subjects, it's juicing the past\Nand regret over the past and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.08,0:07:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing the future.\NUh just like it it loves controversy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because controversy is full of uh ego\Njuice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh when if you're really interested\Nin in becoming enlightened, then it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.80,0:08:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,means to let go uh the mind. itself. Let\Ngo all conceptual thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop talking about phenomena.\NStop u
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,wording it, picturing it. And you become\Nyou you you back up into
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the self as a silent presence. Silent\Npresence of what? Silence presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer witness aspect of\Nconsciousness itself. Eventually you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that that that which is\Nconsciousness, that which is the self
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S are one and the same\Nthing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.95,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Self is nothing but an aspect reflection\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, in a specific definition.\N>> So in other words, quit verbalizing or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.95,0:09:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about enlightenment and start\Nexperiencing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.60,0:09:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, you're trying to get off the\Nthinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right? So, um, what you do is you\Nrehearse it. You have to go back into
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole narrative,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.00,0:09:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There's some new words in our\Nvocabulary. Narrative is one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.00,0:09:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we all grew up with the story\Nof things, now it's a narrative. You
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,know, it's more fashionable.\NAnd I like to stay fashionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.08,0:09:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Say with narrative.\N>> You want to be in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I want to be I don't want any stories\Nanymore. I just want the narrative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear it all the time.\N>> New new thing, you know, narrative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's new words all the time that\Ndidn't exist when I grew up. There's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.76,0:09:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,another common one in politics called\Nvetting. Well, he hasn't been vetted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.95,0:09:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,yet. Or wait till he gets vetted. I\Ndon't think it's even in the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it vetted? I never heard of it. I\Nlived 80 years without ever hearing the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,word vetted. And suddenly it's\Neverything has to be vetted and this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,candidate has to be vetted and wait till\Nhe gets vetted. Is that a real word?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That a real word?\N>> Yeah, it is. I see someone's shaking
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,their head out. Yeah.\N>> I don't know where it got invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.16,0:10:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do you think it's in the dictionary?\N>> Vested.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Vetted. Yeah.\N>> Is it vetted or vested?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.07,0:10:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No. Vetted. Vetted.\N>> Vetted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.68,0:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Vetted.\Nwith a T.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't know. I think it's a I think\Nit's a neologism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think it's a neologism\Nwith no intrinsic historic reality
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.68,0:10:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,vocabulary viewpoint.\N>> Well, you've come out with a few new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.64,0:10:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,words like hermeneutics.\NEpistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.39,0:10:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The hermeneutics.\N>> Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the hermeneutics of relativistic\Nepistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.68,0:11:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's just normal English.\N>> Yeah. Anybody got a dictionary? Look
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that one up.\N>> Well, those are real words. Those are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.51,0:11:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,real words. Those are not neologisms\Nlike vetting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I What's epistemology?\N>> It's in the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.56,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, it is. Okay. You got to get one of\Nthose big ones to look these up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Vetting is in there.\N>> I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm gonna take it up with my congressman\Nwith their vetting is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.20,0:11:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> really the American way. It doesn't\Nsound American to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.92,0:11:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, so getting back then, we live in the\NSo, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to train ourselves to live in\Nthe present,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the past, not in the future, but\Njust in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we do that then then are we\Nliving in the present of joy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I wouldn't say it's the present of\Nanything. It's just living in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.20,0:12:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,present. And and living in the present\Nis is free of negative emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Because you're not anticipating
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.72,0:12:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. You're not wanting to change\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to constantly let going to\Nchange things or make them different
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and um decline the ego's offer of trying\Nto juice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The ego is always trying to juice\Nthings. That's why we have such a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.24,0:12:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,struggle for moral superiority.\NYou know, my folks were more wrong than
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.88,0:12:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,yours. Oh yeah. Oh my mine were wrong.\NMore wrong than yours. I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.39,0:12:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the fight for moral superiority. Who's\Nthe most wronged? Because if you're the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,most wrong, then you're the most\Njustified in hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.00,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Like mom likes you best.\N>> Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> oh.\N>> You're mom's favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:12:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh\N>> oh. Now you're in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> See, that's what I mean. Those are the\Nkind of things that, you know, your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.88,0:13:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to\N>> hang up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.68,0:13:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Well, I you ask yourself, what is what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what what is the ego getting out of\Nthis?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. You know, it's a it's strictly\Nnarcissism
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.12,0:13:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to juice the both the future and\Nthe past
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.60,0:13:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh for excitement for one thing.\N>> Can you live without the excitement of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.76,0:13:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipating the worst possible effect,\Nyou know? Yeah. And uh so what what is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it that you have to let go of to to make\Nthe time mind stop?
