Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.11,0:56:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you look how ineffective the ad is you\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.48,0:56:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> the the world then you know we should\Nwear all the troubles and the everything
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.24,0:56:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,like a like a light garment\N>> I think so
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.28,0:56:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and\N>> forget about all the pain and
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.64,0:56:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> suffering and know that we're not going\Nto change that that it's been in the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.52,0:56:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,world for many many years that's the\Nkarma of being a human
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.92,0:57:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can make their suffering maybe\Neasier and that's about the best we can
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.44,0:57:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,do because of their karmic potential\N>> if we accept that that's the way the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.92,0:57:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,world is and that the world is actually\Nfulfilling its purpose all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.92,0:57:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it it's evolutionary\Nand uh the will of God is expressed as
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.68,0:57:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as the world and its evolution.\NSo consciousness, humanness are all
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.31,0:57:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary\Nand by being evolutionary they are the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.20,0:57:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,per perfect fulfillment of the will of\NGod. Is not the will of God to be
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.83,0:57:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly learning, expanding, uh\Nevolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.07,0:57:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh\Nthat's the way we seem to be created. We
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.20,0:57:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,don't stand still for two seconds. We're\Nconstantly moving, evolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.11,0:57:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Mother Teresa I mean her you\Nknow she she went into the depths of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.31,0:58:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Kolkata and and saved well not saved uh\Nshe actually saved souls not lives
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.55,0:58:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> is basically what she was doing. She was\Nletting the soul cross over.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.83,0:58:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> She was with her soul\N>> right because she worked among the very
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.00,0:58:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ill. Yeah, indeed.\N>> They had none nothing. I mean, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.68,0:58:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,no\N>> people are totally gone and nobody to be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.96,0:58:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with them. So, she was with them to the\Nend.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.16,0:58:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, they knew they were loved\Nright to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.31,0:58:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> So, in other words, don't you think she
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.59,0:58:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was I mean, she couldn't save the body,\Nbut she was saving the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.04,0:58:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. Because when you look within that\Nbeing and connect with the reality of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.24,0:58:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,their self, then they know that who they\Nare is being recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.40,0:58:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember patients brought up\Nwrapped up in ropes and god knows what
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.64,0:59:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,brought in and dumped on the floor of\Nthe hospital and the hopelessness and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.28,0:59:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the agony. And then when you looked at\Nthem,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.35,0:59:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the a caringness arises from within.\NIt's impersonal and the self of the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.72,0:59:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,other person rises because it's been\Nacknowledged. Then you see that their
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.16,0:59:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering has stopped.\N>> The suffering stops in that instant. The
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.00,0:59:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of who they are has been\Nrecognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.16,0:59:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So\N>> I'm sure that's what happened with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.48,0:59:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So even though she might not have saved\Nthe body, she actually saved the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.52,0:59:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. That's all that matters. What\Nhappened to the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.55,0:59:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One job you can get on the other side is\Nto be a greeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.72,0:59:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good job being a greeter.\NAnd as people come across,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.31,0:59:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you reassure them that they are not\Ndead, that they are where they are loved
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.28,0:59:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the you know like a greeter on the\Ndoorway of heaven. You know, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.83,1:00:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have a sign says greeter.\N>> Are you going to be there for all of us?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.59,1:00:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, yes. I've been a greeter. I've never\Nbeen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.96,1:00:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think being a greeter, well, I've been\Na greeter in this world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.48,1:00:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, being a greeter is very\Nfulfilling because people die in agony
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.11,1:00:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for Lauren, abandonment, all hope, uh\Nself-hatred, I'm not worth saving, grief
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.00,1:00:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,over, why did I do this, and so most you\Na lot of people die in a state of agony,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.64,1:00:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's spiritual agony. Spiritual\Nagony. And when you greet them with the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.40,1:00:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,truth of who they really are and the\Nrecognition of who they are, then the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.96,1:00:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,joy springs forth again. So the soul\Nthat's so
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.44,1:00:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,depressed and hopeless and for, you\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.31,1:00:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it it's recognized for its reality.\N>> So I think being a greeter on the other
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.52,1:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,side is one of the greatest jobs you can\Nget.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.00,1:01:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The car runs over them and they're\Nscreaming in pain and agony and oh God,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.35,1:01:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how could you abandon me? And all of a\Nsudden they fall into the arms of a
